Replace libcwd::_private_::debug_objects_ct with something using `threadsafe::Unlocked` instead of the DEBUG_*_(ACQUIRE|RELEASE)_*_LOCK macros. It seems that replacing
```
 public:
  typedef std::vector<debug_ct*> container_type;
 private:
  container_type* WNS_debug_objects;
```
with:
```
 public:
  using container_t = threadsafe::Unlocked<std::vector<debug_ct*>, threadsafe::policy::ReadWrite<AIReadWriteMutex>>;
 private:
  container_t WNS_debug_objects;
```
might be a good start.
